    <dc:date opf:event="modification">2025-05-27</dc:date>
  <description xmlns="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">&lt;b&gt;A probing investigation of Southeast Asia&amp;rsquo;s online scam industry &amp;ndash; told through the voices of survivors&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Running the gamut from the infamous &amp;lsquo;pig butchering&amp;rsquo; romance con to sophisticated online extortion and investment fraud, Southeast Asia has emerged as the global hub for cybercrime. Based on years of field research, &lt;i&gt;Scam &lt;/i&gt;takes an in-depth look at the history and inner dynamics of the region&amp;rsquo;s online scam industry. Revealed are the appalling working conditions &amp;mdash; akin to modern slavery &amp;mdash; in the hundreds of prisonlike compounds that have mushroomed throughout multiple countries. The result is a shocking expos&amp;eacute; of victims forced to be perpetrators, a tragic modern tale.</description>
</metadata>
